sec.p:
An anonymized dataset using only key variables from the ComPAS trial was used for this analysis [40]. The variables included case ID, age, sex, date of visit, anthropometric measurements (MUAC, weight, height, WAZ, HAZ) and oedema at each visit, outcome (recovered, died, defaulted, transferred or early discharge), site code, and intervention code (standard or combined protocol). Morbidity, hospitalization, fat mass, and fat-free mass variables were used from the follow-up study dataset. The following categorizations and anthropometric cut-offs were used:
Group 1: MUAC < 11.5 cm and WAZ ≥ −3;
Group 2: MUAC between 11.5 cm and <12.5 cm and WAZ < −3;
Group 3: MUAC < 11.5 cm and WAZ < −3;
Group 4: MUAC between 11.5 cm and <12.5 cm and WAZ ≥ −3.0.
